FCC ID L9VAR-5389 redirects (CoI) to KA2DSL-2640U.
"PWB:T0047805C-G" and "DAT:"<10? covered by a label>".08.18" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :The FCC sample label seems to indicate the internal '''DareGlobal''' model for the device is TA04G-N2GDM-HA01. The SoC is covered by a heatsink in the FCC photos, but it is presumed to be a '''Broadcom''' chip. The Wi-Fi radio is shown as using a [http://www.skyworksinc.com/Product.aspx?ProductID=962 '''Skyworks''' ('''SiGe''') SE2603L / 2603L 802.11b/g/n WLAN Front End Module].
Default settings are per the FCC manual. They may be inaccurate. :The sample SSID in the manual is '''Comtrend8C61''' ('''ComtrendXXXX''' pattern).
